<section class="project-hero">
  <div class="project-status">
    <span class="status-badge">Active Development</span>
    <a href="{{ site.github }}/venturi" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="github-link">
      View on GitHub →
    </a>
  </div>
  
  <div class="project-overview">
    <p class="lead">
      Venturi is a media streaming server built from the ground up in modern C++. 
      Named after the Venturi effect—where fluid speeds up through a constriction—it's 
      designed to efficiently channel media data to clients.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="project-section">
  <h2>Technical Overview</h2>
  
  <div class="tech-details">
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Architecture</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Built on <strong>Boost.Beast</strong> for HTTP handling</li>
        <li><strong>Boost.Asio</strong> for asynchronous I/O</li>
        <li>Modern C++20 features throughout</li>
        <li>Single-threaded event loop (scalable design planned)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Current Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>HTTP/1.1 byte-range request support</li>
        <li>Efficient MP4 file serving</li>
        <li>Seekable video streaming</li>
        <li>Proper MIME type handling</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Planned Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>HLS/DASH adaptive streaming</li>
        <li>Multi-threaded request handling</li>
        <li>Caching layer</li>
        <li>Metrics and monitoring</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="project-section">
  <h2>Why This Project?</h2>
  
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Media streaming sits at a fascinating intersection of systems programming 
      and real-world user experience. Every millisecond of latency matters. 
      Every byte of bandwidth costs money. The constraints force elegant solutions.
    </p>
    <p>
      Building Venturi lets me explore:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Network programming</strong> — TCP, HTTP, connection management</li>
      <li><strong>Performance optimization</strong> — Zero-copy I/O, memory management</li>
      <li><strong>Media formats</strong> — Container formats, codecs, streaming protocols</li>
      <li><strong>Systems design</strong> — Scalability, reliability, observability</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

